summary:
What if...we enable the Women of Myanmar to become more entrepreneurial and creative?
WOM is a training opportunity for women in Myanmar. Women follow a two year program that will lead to deployability in entrepreneurship and/or intrapreneurship in International Business. The program focuses on vocational training in entrepreneurial skills by making assignments (society/business), coaching of personal development, short traineeships in several environments and matchmaking to start a business or to get the right woman on the right job. Women acquire an entrepreneurial attitude (pro-active thinking, problemsolving, curiosity) and they gain competence in enterpreneurial skills like communication, strategy, sale, finance.
The targetgroup is women who accomplished at least secondary school and have a clear ambition and potential to be part of the upcoming success of the emergent market Myanmar. 

These are the objectives at the end of the program:
women will find a job at the local or international business
women are ready to start a business of her own
